(\Omega,\mathcal{A},\mu,T)
\forall B\in\mathcal{A}: T^{-1}B\subset B\implies \mu(B)\in\left\{0,1\right\}
(1)\implies (2)
B\in\mathcal{A}
T^{-1}B\subset B
\mu(T^{-1}B)=\mu(B)
T^{-1}B\subset B
T^{-1}B\Delta B=B\setminus T^{-1}(B)
\mu(T^{-1}(B))=\mu(B)<\infty
B
T
\mu(B)\in\left\{0,1\right\}
 \mu(T^{-1}B\Delta B)=\mu(B\setminus T^{-1}B)=\mu(B)-\mu(T^{-1}B)=\mu(B)-\mu(B)=0. 
(2)\implies (1)
